 test source code location for this index entry. Use `$version$` as the placeholder for this entry's `metadata-version` in versioned URLs.\\ndocs/CONTRIBUTING.md:111:* `documentation-url`: URL to the project documentation for this index entry. Use `$version$` as the placeholder for this entry's `metadata-version` in versioned URLs.\\ndocs/CONTRIBUTING.md:122:    \\\"metadata-version\\\": \\\"1.0.0\\\",\\ndocs/CONTRIBUTING.md:138:     \\\"metadata-version\\\": \\\"1.1.0\\\",\\nmetadata/com.google.re2j/re2j/index.json:4:    \\\"metadata-version\\\" : \\\"1.1\\\",\\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.exposed/exposed-json/index.json:4:    \\\"metadata-version\\\" : \\\"1.2.0\\\",\\ndocs/support/index.html:586:          if (entry[\\\"metadata-version\\\"]) {\\ndocs/support/index.html:587:            versions.add(entry[\\\"metadata-version\\\"]);\\ndocs/support/index.html:649:            metadataValue(\\\"Latest metadata\\\", latest[\\\"metadata-version\\\"]),\\ndocs/support/index.html:666:            metadataValue(\\\"Metadata version\\\", latest[\\\"metadata-version\\\"]),\\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:43:- A directory tree under `metadata/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/` containing JSON files in the format described by GraalVM's [Native Image Manual Configuration](https://www.graalvm.org/latest/reference-manual/native-image/dynamic-features/Reflection/#manual-configuration) reference.\\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:46:- A `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/stats.json` mirror of per-version metrics (dynamic-access call sites, coverage, lines of code, dependency information).\\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:52:- Validation of `index.json` schema and `metadata-version`/`tested-versions` integrity.\\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:57:The harness uses a single coordinates filter `-Pcoordinates=` accepting `all`, `group:artifact`, `group:artifact:version`, or shard `k/n`. It also exposes authoring helpers (`generateMetadata`, `splitTestOnlyMetadata`, `fixTestNativeImageRun`, `addTestedVersion`, `fetchExistingLibrariesWithNewerVersions`), reporting tasks (`jacocoTestReport`, `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport`, `generateLibraryStats`, `analyzeExternalLibraryDynamicAccess`), and the `package` release task. The full task reference lives in [DEVELOPING.md](DEVELOPING.md).\\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:155:<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/\\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:161:**2. `<groupId>/<artifactId>/index.json`** — one per supported artifact, schema [metadata-library-index-schema-v2.0.1.json](../metadata/schemas/metadata-library-index-schema-v2.0.1.json). It is a JSON **array** of entries; each entry's required fields are `metadata-version`, `tested-versions`, and `allowed-packages`, with optional `default-for` (Java regex), `latest: true`, `override: true`, `requires: [\\\"<group>:<artifact>\\\", …]`, `test-version`, `skipped-versions`, `language`, and the four URL fields. Plugin-relevant fields are the first six.\\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:165:**3. `<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/reachability-metadata.json`** — the only file the plugin loads at native-image time. Schema [reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json](../metadata/schemas/reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json) (a vendored copy of the upstream GraalVM schema), with top-level keys `reflection`, `jni`, `resources`, `bundles`, `serialization`, and `foreignCalls`. Every entry must carry a `condition.typeReachable` clause (FR-M-2) so the plugin can rely on conditional registration. The legacy split-config layout (`reflect-config.json`, `jni-config.json`, …) is no longer present.\\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:169:1. `v ∈ tested-versions` → use that entry's `metadata-version` directory directly.\\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:178:    Tested -- yes --> UseTested[\\\"Use that entry's<br/><code>metadata-version/</code>\\\"]\\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:180:    DefaultFor -- yes --> UseDefault[\\\"Use that entry's<br/><code>metadata-version/</code>\\\"]\\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:184:    Latest -- yes --> UseLatest[\\\"Use that entry's<br/><code>metadata-version/</code>\\\"]\\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:207:- **FR-M-7** Metadata can declare dependencies on other artifacts via `requires`. Test-only metadata must be moved to the test resources file (via `splitTestOnlyMetadata`).\\ndocs/CI.md:31:  - Uses: [`generateChangedTestedVersionsMatrix`](../tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle) to compute only newly added [`tested-versions`](../metadata/com.google.protobuf/protobuf-java-util/index.json) from the base/head diff and pairs them with the matching [`metadata-version`](../metadata/com.google.protobuf/protobuf-java-util/index.json), then runs [`run-consecutive-tests.sh`](../.github/workflows/scripts/run-consecutive-tests.sh) only for those added versions.\\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.exposed/exposed-kotlin-datetime/index.json:4:    \\\"metadata-version\\\" : \\\"1.2.0\\\",\\nmetadata/org.apache.httpcomponents.core5/httpcore5/index.json:4:    \\\"metadata-version\\\" : \\\"5.2\\\",\\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/TckExtensionTests.java:39:                    \\\"metadata-version\\\": \\\"1.0.0\\\",\\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/TckExtensionTests.java:66:                    \\\"metadata-version\\\": \\\"1.0.0\\\",\\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/TckExtensionTests.java:110:                    \\\"metadata-version\\\": \\\"1.0.0\\\",\\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/TckExtensionTests.java:139:                    \\\"metadata-version\\\": \\\"1.0.0\\\",\\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/TckExtensionTests.java:177:                    \\\"metadata-version\\\": \\\"1.0.0\\\",\\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/TckExtensionTests.java:194:                    \\\"metadata-version\\\": \\\"2.0.0\\\",\\nmetadata